The number of Americans filing initial unemployment insurance claims has reached its lowest level since the start of the pandemic. Since President Biden took office in January, the average number of claims has decreased from over 830,000 to below 378,000. The economy has also generated over 4 million jobs, surpassing any previous administration. Additionally, the economy is experiencing its fastest growth in the first half of a year in almost four decades. This positive news highlights the success of the economic recovery, which has been supported by the American Rescue Plan. However, the recovery is still ongoing, and challenges such as the Delta variant of COVID-19 remain. Despite these challenges, President Biden's plan to promote economic growth for all Americans is yielding tangible results for workers.